#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
OCI Streaming to Telegraf InfluxDB Line Protocol Converter

This script continuously consumes metrics from an Oracle Cloud Infrastructure (OCI) Streaming stream
and outputs them in the Telegraf InfluxDB line protocol format for consumption by Telegraf.

The script implements a multi-threaded consumer architecture that:
- Reads raw metrics from one or more stream partitions
- Aggregates metrics by minute intervals with configurable windows
- Applies appropriate aggregation functions (sum, mean, count) per metric type
- Outputs aggregated metrics to stdout in InfluxDB line protocol format

Architecture:
    1. Consumer threads read messages from OCI Streaming partitions
    2. Raw metrics are placed in a shared queue
    3. Aggregator thread processes metrics from the queue
    4. Metrics are aggregated by timestamp minute and dimensions
    5. Aggregated metrics are emitted when they fall outside the aggregation window
    6. Timeout mechanism ensures stale metrics are emitted

Environment Variables:
    OCI_CONFIG_PATH: Path to OCI configuration file (optional). If not set, instance principal
                     authentication will be attempted.
    OCI_PROFILE: OCI profile name to use from config file (default: "DEFAULT")
    GROUP_NAME: Consumer group name for stream consumption (default: "telegraf")
    MESSAGES_ENDPOINT: Streaming service endpoint URL (optional, auto-discovered if not set)
    STREAM_OCID: OCID of the stream to consume from (default: Jinja2 template variable)
    OCI_REGION: OCI region identifier. If not set, will be auto-detected from instance metadata.
    METRIC_AGGREGATION_WINDOW_MINUTES: Window size for metric aggregation in minutes (default: 2)
    METRIC_AGGREGATION_TIMEOUT: Timeout for emitting stale metrics in minutes (default: 10)
    STREAM_READ_INTERVAL: Seconds to wait between stream reads (default: 0.5)

Usage:
    Run as a standalone script (typically invoked by Telegraf exec input plugin):
        $ python3 oci_metrics_telegraf_streaming_input.py

    The script outputs metrics to stdout in InfluxDB line protocol format:
        <measurement>,<tag_key>=<tag_value> <field_key>=<field_value> <timestamp_ns>

Metric Aggregation:
    Different metrics use different aggregation functions:
    - Sum: Counters and cumulative metrics (e.g., bytes, packets, operations)
    - Mean: Gauges and averages (e.g., throughput, utilization percentages)
    - Count: Event counts (e.g., number of operations)

    The metric_stats dictionary defines the aggregation function for each metric type.

Graceful Shutdown:
    - SIGHUP signal triggers graceful shutdown
    - Ctrl+C (KeyboardInterrupt) also triggers graceful shutdown
"""

